header.gameNote: ATLANTIC SUN TR AT JOHNSON CITY TN

article.headline: Campbell 90, Jacksonville 85
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- Eric Smith hit a pair of 3-pointers and two free throws in overtime to help sixth-seeded Campbell upset third-seeded Jacksonville with a 90-85 win Thursday in the quarterfinals of the Atlantic Sun Conference tournament. Smith finished with 22 points and Campbell (14-16) advanced to take on Belmont in Fridays second semifinal. Jacksonville (15-14) trailed 72-63 with just under five minutes left in regulation, but rallied to tie the game at 78-78 on Jesse Kimbroughs difficult shot in the lane with 1.3 seconds to go. In overtime, Smith broke the ice with a 3-pointer at 3:08 and then hit another with 2:21 to go to make it 84-81. He followed with a pair of free throws at 1:41, giving the Camels an 86-83 lead that the Dolphins couldn't overcome. The game was back and forth during the first half, but Campbell had an 8-0 run in the last 1:10 to take a 44-38 edge at the half. Jonathan Rodriguez scored 21 points and grabbed 11 rebounds for Campbell while Jake Wohlfeil added 11 points and Kyle Vejraska 10. Ledell Eackles added a career-high 10 rebounds. Jacksonville got 24 points and six assists from Kimbrough while Lehmon Colbert added 15 points and Ben Smith totaled 14. Marcus Allen had 10 points and 10 rebounds.
